                            <comment id="14476739" author="melix" created="Tue, 4 Nov 2014 06:02:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is actually a bug in the proxy generator. It can be reproduces outside of the context of traits with this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; DoStuff {
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {
   void foo(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; a, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; b) {}
}

def gp=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo() as DoStuff
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In any case, runtime traits will generate a proxy, meaning that even if I fix (and I will) this bug, the code won&apos;t work as is, because the assignment will fail. See &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.groovy-lang.org/latest/html/documentation/core-traits.html#_runtime_implementation_of_traits&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://docs.groovy-lang.org/latest/html/documentation/core-traits.html#_runtime_implementation_of_traits&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed explanation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
